-loop
get input
check if valid
	if not vaild
		prompt user to enter filename again.
ask if user has more input
	if false
		break

-loop

prompt for location of output backup file
check if input is vaild
	if not prompt again

ask user if compression should or should not be applied
	if true
		apply compression
	if false
		just archive

create tar file containing all files that the user entered
report that script has completed.
